					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<extent>130 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>240</height>
										<width>170</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>160</height>
										<width>115</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>130 folios (+ 3 modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and 4 at the end). Folio 1 is a paper flyleaf.</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>13 complete quires of 8 and 10 leaves, and 1 incomplete quire of 8 leaves at the end. </p>
									<p>Catchwords, marking the end of the quires, partially cut away in the trimming.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Incomplete at the end.</p>
									<p>Stained.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1" ruledLines="23" writtenLines="23">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Visible hard-point ruling.</p>
									<p>Hair-side and flesh-side of the folios distinguishable.</p>
									<p>Last line written outside ruling.</p>
									<p>Chapter initials given in larger characters. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Italian semi-cursive script of the 15th century. </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folio 2r: a notice of the presentation of the manuscript by <name type="person" role="owner">῾Azariah Ḥayim ben Sanguinetti</name> to <name type="person" role="owner">Yosef ῾Azulai</name>, in cursive Sefardi script.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Yitsḥaḳ Leṿi</name>: inscribed in an Italian cursive scipt (folio 2r).</p>
							<p>Censored by <name type="person" role="censor">Dominico Irosolomitano</name>, Italian censor (active in the last quarter of the 16th and first quarter of the 17th century): inscribed with his name, 1597 (folio 130v); see <ref target="Popper_1969" type="page">61</ref> , and appendix § 62-74. </p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
